✅ Commands & Simple Explanations
1. vim statefulset.yml

Open or edit the StatefulSet YAML file.

2. vim namespace.yml

Open or edit the Namespace YAML file.

3. kubectl apply -f namespace.yml

Create the namespace defined in namespace.yml.

4. kubectl get ns

List all namespaces in the cluster.

5. kubectl get mysql

Invalid command — mysql is not a Kubernetes resource.

6. kubectl get ns mysql

Show the details of the mysql namespace.

7. vim service.yml

Open or edit the Service YAML.

8. kubectl apply -f service.yml

Create the Service for the StatefulSet (usually a headless service).

9. kubectl apply -f statefulset.yml

Create/Update the StatefulSet from the YAML.

10. cat statefulset.yml

Print contents of the file (to verify changes).

11. cat > statefulset.yml

Overwrite the file with new content (until Ctrl+D).

12. kubectl get all -n nginx

Show all Kubernetes objects in the nginx namespace.

13. kubectl get all -n mysql

Show all objects in the mysql namespace (pods, svc, replicaset, etc).

14. watch kubectl get all -n mysql

Continuously watch all resources in the mysql namespace (auto-refresh).

15. kubectl get pod -n mysql

List all pods in the mysql namespace.

16. kubectl exec -it mysql-statefulset-0 -n mysql -- bash

Enter the MySQL pod's shell (bash) of the first replica (ordinal 0).

17. kubectl delete pod mysql-statefulset-0 -n mysql

Manually delete a pod.
→ StatefulSet will recreate it automatically.

18. kubectl get all -n mysql

Check resources again.

19. history

Show command history.
